description: Starts the reprocessing of raw message data through the pipeline.

parameters.name: pipelineName
parameters.description: The name of the pipeline on which to start reprocessing.

parameters.name: startTime
parameters.description: The start time (inclusive) of raw message data that is reprocessed. If you specify a value for the startTime parameter, you must not use the channelMessages object.

parameters.name: endTime
parameters.description: The end time (exclusive) of raw message data that is reprocessed. If you specify a value for the endTime parameter, you must not use the channelMessages object.

parameters.name: channelMessages
parameters.description: Specifies one or more sets of channel messages that you want to reprocess. If you use the channelMessages object, you must not specify a value for startTime and endTime. s3Paths (list) --- Specifies one or more keys that identify the Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3) objects that save your channel messages. You must use the full path for the key. Example path: channel/mychannel/__dt=2020-02-29 00:00:00/1582940490000_1582940520000_123456789012_mychannel_0_2118.0.json.gz (string) ---

nested_params.name: s3Paths
nested_params.description: Specifies one or more keys that identify the Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3) objects that save your channel messages. You must use the full path for the key. Example path: channel/mychannel/__dt=2020-02-29 00:00:00/1582940490000_1582940520000_123456789012_mychannel_0_2118.0.json.gz.

nested_items.name: reprocessingId
nested_items.description: The ID of the pipeline reprocessing activity that was started.
